[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 7509,
        "end_time": 9317,
        "text": "We have some good reasons to completely"
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 9317,
        "end_time": 11235,
        "text": "switch over to solar power."
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 11235,
        "end_time": 12859,
        "text": "It&#39;s cheaper in many cases,"
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 12859,
        "end_time": 14809,
        "text": "and definitely more sustainable"
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 14809,
        "end_time": 17213,
        "text": "than our dependance on traditional power plants"
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 17213,
        "end_time": 18906,
        "text": "that use resources like coal,"
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 18906,
        "end_time": 20950,
        "text": "which will eventually run out."
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 20950,
        "end_time": 22035,
        "text": "So why don&#39;t we replace these"
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 22035,
        "end_time": 24570,
        "text": "traditional plants with solar energy?"
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 24570,
        "end_time": 26027,
        "text": "Because there&#39;s one factor that makes"
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 26027,
        "end_time": 28476,
        "text": "solar power very unpredictable:"
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 28476,
        "end_time": 30052,
        "text": "cloud cover."
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 30052,
        "end_time": 32223,
        "text": "As the sun&#39;s rays move towards Earth,"
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 32223,
        "end_time": 34652,
        "text": "some get absorbed by the Earth&#39;s atmosphere,"
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 34652,
        "end_time": 36755,
        "text": "some are reflected back into outer space,"
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 36755,
        "end_time": 39887,
        "text": "but the rest make it to the Earth&#39;s surface."
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 39887,
        "end_time": 41436,
        "text": "The ones that aren&#39;t deviated"
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 41436,
        "end_time": 43516,
        "text": "are called direct irradiance."
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 43516,
        "end_time": 45359,
        "text": "The ones that are deflected by clouds"
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 45359,
        "end_time": 47659,
        "text": "are called diffuse irradiance."
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 47659,
        "end_time": 50509,
        "text": "And those rays that first get reflected by a surface,"
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 50509,
        "end_time": 51780,
        "text": "like a nearby building,"
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 51780,
        "end_time": 54379,
        "text": "before reaching the solar energy system"
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 54379,
        "end_time": 56610,
        "text": "are called reflected irradiance."
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 56610,
        "end_time": 58256,
        "text": "But before we can examine how clouds"
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 58256,
        "end_time": 61281,
        "text": "affect the sun&#39;s rays and electricity production,"
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 61281,
        "end_time": 64500,
        "text": "let&#39;s see how these solar energy systems work."
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 64500,
        "end_time": 66868,
        "text": "First up, we have solar towers."
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 66868,
        "end_time": 68414,
        "text": "These are made up of a central tower"
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 68414,
        "end_time": 71120,
        "text": "surrounded by a huge field of mirrors"
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 71120,
        "end_time": 73034,
        "text": "that track the sun&#39;s path and focus"
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 73034,
        "end_time": 76651,
        "text": "only the direct rays onto a single point on the tower,"
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 76651,
        "end_time": 79434,
        "text": "kind of like an eager beachgoer."
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 79434,
        "end_time": 81130,
        "text": "The heat generated by these rays"
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 81130,
        "end_time": 84706,
        "text": "is so immense that it can be used to boil water"
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 84706,
        "end_time": 87720,
        "text": "producing steam that drives a traditional turbine,"
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 87720,
        "end_time": 89545,
        "text": "which makes electricity."
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 89545,
        "end_time": 91515,
        "text": "But when we say solar energy systems,"
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 91515,
        "end_time": 94252,
        "text": "we&#39;re usually talking about photovoltaics,"
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 94252,
        "end_time": 95704,
        "text": "or solar panels,"
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 95704,
        "end_time": 97325,
        "text": "which are the systems most commonly used"
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 97325,
        "end_time": 98945,
        "text": "to generate solar power."
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 98945,
        "end_time": 99916,
        "text": "In solar panels,"
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 99916,
        "end_time": 102795,
        "text": "photons from the sun&#39;s rays hit the surface of a panel,"
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 102795,
        "end_time": 104465,
        "text": "and electrons are released"
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 104465,
        "end_time": 106818,
        "text": "to get an electric current going."
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 106818,
        "end_time": 109818,
        "text": "Solar panels can use all types of irradiance,"
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 109818,
        "end_time": 113556,
        "text": "while solar towers can only use direct irradiance,"
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 113556,
        "end_time": 116218,
        "text": "and this is where clouds become important"
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 116218,
        "end_time": 118290,
        "text": "because depending on their type and location"
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 118290,
        "end_time": 119537,
        "text": "relative to the sun,"
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 119537,
        "end_time": 121645,
        "text": "they can either increase or decrease"
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 121645,
        "end_time": 124122,
        "text": "the amount of electricity produced."
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 124122,
        "end_time": 126236,
        "text": "For instance, even a few cumulus clouds"
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 126236,
        "end_time": 127690,
        "text": "in front of the sun can reduce"
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 127690,
        "end_time": 130042,
        "text": "the electricity production in solar towers"
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 130042,
        "end_time": 134461,
        "text": "to almost zero because of this dependence on direct rays."
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 134461,
        "end_time": 136693,
        "text": "In solar panels, those clouds would decrease"
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 136693,
        "end_time": 138200,
        "text": "energy output as well,"
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 138200,
        "end_time": 139435,
        "text": "though not as much"
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 139435,
        "end_time": 142710,
        "text": "because solar panels can use all types of irradiance."
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 142710,
        "end_time": 146160,
        "text": "However, all this depends on the clouds exact positioning."
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 146160,
        "end_time": 148468,
        "text": "Due to reflection, or a particular phenomeon"
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 148468,
        "end_time": 150344,
        "text": "called Mie scattering,"
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 150344,
        "end_time": 153125,
        "text": "the sun&#39;s rays can actually be focused forward"
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 153125,
        "end_time": 156566,
        "text": "by clouds to create a more than 50% increase"
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 156566,
        "end_time": 159681,
        "text": "in the solar irradiance reaching a solar panel."
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 159681,
        "end_time": 162231,
        "text": "If this potential increase isn&#39;t accounted for,"
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 162231,
        "end_time": 164780,
        "text": "it could damage the solar panel."
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 164780,
        "end_time": 165901,
        "text": "Why does this matter?"
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 165901,
        "end_time": 167731,
        "text": "Well, you wouldn&#39;t want this lesson to stop"
    },
    {
        "index": 72,
        "start_time": 167731,
        "end_time": 171127,
        "text": "just because a cloud passed over the panel on your roof."
    },
    {
        "index": 73,
        "start_time": 171127,
        "end_time": 174429,
        "text": "In solar towers, huge tanks of molten salt or oil"
    },
    {
        "index": 74,
        "start_time": 174429,
        "end_time": 176808,
        "text": "can be used to store any excess heat"
    },
    {
        "index": 75,
        "start_time": 176808,
        "end_time": 178292,
        "text": "and use it when needed,"
    },
    {
        "index": 76,
        "start_time": 178292,
        "end_time": 179736,
        "text": "so that&#39;s how they manage the problem"
    },
    {
        "index": 77,
        "start_time": 179736,
        "end_time": 182525,
        "text": "of fluctuating solar irradiance to smooth out"
    },
    {
        "index": 78,
        "start_time": 182525,
        "end_time": 183999,
        "text": "electricity production."
    },
    {
        "index": 79,
        "start_time": 183999,
        "end_time": 185345,
        "text": "But in the case of solar panels,"
    },
    {
        "index": 80,
        "start_time": 185345,
        "end_time": 187905,
        "text": "there currently isn&#39;t any way to affordably"
    },
    {
        "index": 81,
        "start_time": 187905,
        "end_time": 189730,
        "text": "store extra energy."
    },
    {
        "index": 82,
        "start_time": 189730,
        "end_time": 191717,
        "text": "That&#39;s where traditional power plants come in"
    },
    {
        "index": 83,
        "start_time": 191717,
        "end_time": 193841,
        "text": "because to correct for any fluctuations"
    },
    {
        "index": 84,
        "start_time": 193841,
        "end_time": 195815,
        "text": "in these solar powered plants,"
    },
    {
        "index": 85,
        "start_time": 195815,
        "end_time": 198149,
        "text": "extra electricity from traditional sources"
    },
    {
        "index": 86,
        "start_time": 198149,
        "end_time": 200429,
        "text": "always needs to be available."
    },
    {
        "index": 87,
        "start_time": 200429,
        "end_time": 202869,
        "text": "But then why aren&#39;t these tradtional power plants"
    },
    {
        "index": 88,
        "start_time": 202869,
        "end_time": 204337,
        "text": "just used as a backup,"
    },
    {
        "index": 89,
        "start_time": 204337,
        "end_time": 206075,
        "text": "instead of us humans depending on them"
    },
    {
        "index": 90,
        "start_time": 206075,
        "end_time": 208296,
        "text": "as our main sources of energy?"
    },
    {
        "index": 91,
        "start_time": 208296,
        "end_time": 210113,
        "text": "Because it&#39;s impossible for an employee"
    },
    {
        "index": 92,
        "start_time": 210113,
        "end_time": 212248,
        "text": "at a coal fired or a nuclear plant"
    },
    {
        "index": 93,
        "start_time": 212248,
        "end_time": 213507,
        "text": "to turn a knob to produce"
    },
    {
        "index": 94,
        "start_time": 213507,
        "end_time": 215427,
        "text": "more or less electricity depending"
    },
    {
        "index": 95,
        "start_time": 215427,
        "end_time": 217834,
        "text": "on how many clouds there are in the sky."
    },
    {
        "index": 96,
        "start_time": 217834,
        "end_time": 220521,
        "text": "The response time would simply be too slow."
    },
    {
        "index": 97,
        "start_time": 220521,
        "end_time": 222819,
        "text": "Instead, to accommodate these fluctuations,"
    },
    {
        "index": 98,
        "start_time": 222819,
        "end_time": 225718,
        "text": "some extra electricity from traditional power plants"
    },
    {
        "index": 99,
        "start_time": 225718,
        "end_time": 228036,
        "text": "is always being produced."
    },
    {
        "index": 100,
        "start_time": 228036,
        "end_time": 229496,
        "text": "On clear sky days,"
    },
    {
        "index": 101,
        "start_time": 229496,
        "end_time": 231578,
        "text": "that extra electricity might be wasted,"
    },
    {
        "index": 102,
        "start_time": 231578,
        "end_time": 233557,
        "text": "but when cloudy skies prevail,"
    },
    {
        "index": 103,
        "start_time": 233557,
        "end_time": 235467,
        "text": "it&#39;s what fills the gap."
    },
    {
        "index": 104,
        "start_time": 235467,
        "end_time": 236930,
        "text": "This is what we currently depend on"
    },
    {
        "index": 105,
        "start_time": 236930,
        "end_time": 238861,
        "text": "for a constant supply of energy."
    },
    {
        "index": 106,
        "start_time": 238861,
        "end_time": 240186,
        "text": "For this reason, a lot of researchers"
    },
    {
        "index": 107,
        "start_time": 240186,
        "end_time": 242632,
        "text": "are interested in forcasting the motion"
    },
    {
        "index": 108,
        "start_time": 242632,
        "end_time": 245835,
        "text": "and formation of clouds through satellite images"
    },
    {
        "index": 109,
        "start_time": 245835,
        "end_time": 247883,
        "text": "or cameras that look up at the sky"
    },
    {
        "index": 110,
        "start_time": 247883,
        "end_time": 250765,
        "text": "to maximize the energy from solar power plants"
    },
    {
        "index": 111,
        "start_time": 250765,
        "end_time": 253038,
        "text": "and minimize energy waste."
    },
    {
        "index": 112,
        "start_time": 253038,
        "end_time": 254365,
        "text": "If we could accomplish that,"
    },
    {
        "index": 113,
        "start_time": 254365,
        "end_time": 256484,
        "text": "you&#39;d be able to enjoy this video"
    },
    {
        "index": 114,
        "start_time": 256484,
        "end_time": 258486,
        "text": "powered solely by the sun&#39;s rays,"
    },
    {
        "index": 115,
        "start_time": 258486,
        "end_time": 260067,
        "text": "no matter what the weather,"
    },
    {
        "index": 116,
        "start_time": 260067,
        "end_time": 261845,
        "text": "although if the sun is shining,"
    },
    {
        "index": 117,
        "start_time": 261845,
        "end_time": 264070,
        "text": "you may be tempted to venture outside"
    },
    {
        "index": 118,
        "start_time": 264070,
        "end_time": 267034,
        "text": "to go and do a different kind of cloud gazing."
    }
]